==English==
===Noun===
'''slope''' (''plural'' '''slopes''')

# An area of ground that tends evenly upward or downward.
#: ''I had to climb a small slope to get to the site.''
# The degree to which a surface tends upward or downward.
#: ''The road has a very sharp downward slope at that point.''
# (''mathematics'') In a graph of a quantity ''y'' plotted against a quantity ''x'', the rate of increase of ''y'' with respect to ''x''.
#: ''The slope of a parabola increases linearly.''<!--Is this used of curves, or only of lines?-->
# (''vulgar, highly offensive'') A person of Chinese or other East Asian descent.

====Synonyms====
